//~~ Supported jewels 19,210~240
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//
// ### JewelUpgradeSystem ###
//	Enabled: Deactivates or activates the system, 0/1
//	Extended: Allows to use maximum capabilities of the plugin, should stay enabled, 0/1
//	
// ### JewelUpgradeSystem::IgnoreItemList::Item ###
//	Cat: Category of item, see ItemList.xml
//	Index: Index of item, see ItemList.xml
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//~~ List of items that cannot be converted
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//
// ### JewelUpgradeSystem::Jewel ###
//	Cat: Category of item, always 19
//	Index: Index of item, 210-240
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//~~ Every jewel type can be defined once only, however item applications are infinite
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//
// ### JewelUpgradeSystem::Jewel::Item
//	Cat: Category of item, see ItemList.xml. -1 for any wearable item, supported categories 0~11
//	Index: Index of item, see ItemList.xml
//	ItemMinLevel: Minimum level for item required to be eligible for jewel upgrade
//	ItemMaxLevel: Maximum level for item required to be eligible for jewel upgrade
//	MinExcOpt: Minimum number of excellent options required
//	MaxExcOpt: Maximum number of excellent options required
//	SetItem: Whether required item must be ancient, 0/1
//	Success: Success rate of upgrade, n/100
//	RewardCat: Category of upgrade result item, see ItemList.xml, if item type stays the same, set same as Cat and Index
//	RewardIndex: Index of upgrade result item, see ItemList.xml, if item type stays the same, set same as Cat and Index
//	RewardLevel: Level of upgrade result item, 0-15
//	FailPenalty: In case of failure, different kind of penalties may be applied:
//		~ -1: No penalty
//		~ 0: Destroy item
//		~ 1-15: Reduce item level by random number up to defined value
//
//	RewardSetItem: Set upgrade result item as ancient, 0/1
//	RewardMinExcOpt: Minimum number of new excellent options added to upgrade result item, 0-9
//	RewardSocket: Number of socket slots added to upgrade result item, 0-5
//
// STRICTLY NO COMMENTS INSIDE TAGS
-->

